'''Juan Manuel San Martín Da Costa''' (born 20 January 1994) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Portuguese club [[Louletano D.C.|Louletano]], on loan from [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]].

==Club career==
Born in [[Rivera]], San Martín is a product of [[Peñarol]] youth system, joining them in 2009, at age 15. Two years later, reports in the press informed that he, [[Jim Varela]] and [[Elbio Álvarez]] were joining [[S.L. Benfica]] but the deal was only finalised in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Benfica já controla três promessas do Peñarol|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica-penarol-jorge-jesus-elbio-alvarez-maxi-pereira-paco-casal/520c030e30042d2c8f7cc4fb.html|publisher=Maisfutebol|date=2 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pase de un juvenil generó la golpiza al gerente de Peñarol|url=http://subrayado.com.uy/Site/noticia/20591/pase-de-un-juvenil-genero-la-golpiza-al-gerente-de-penarol|work=subrayado.com.uy|date=29 January 2013}}</ref> The transfer fee was a reported for €2.9 million by some sources,<ref>{{cite news|title=El Karma de las juveniles de Peñarol|url=http://www.elobservadormas.com.uy/noticia/2014/01/13/41/el-karma-de-las-juveniles-de-penarol_269392/|work=elobservadormas.com.uy|date=28 July 2014}}</ref> and €2.4 million by others.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bizera diferenciado, Germinal López debe buscar un abogado|url=http://www.carasycaretas.com.uy/bizera-diferenciado-germinal-lopez-debe-buscar-un-abogado/|work=carasycaretas.com.uy|date=15 August 2013}}</ref>

In 2013, he was loaned to [[S.C. Farense|Farense]], playing 11 league matches, without scoring.<ref>{{cite news|title=Juan Manuel San Martín Da Costa|url=http://www.fichajes.com/jugador/j181040_juan-manuel-san-martin-da-costa|work=fichajes.com}}</ref> He returned to Benfica the following season, being loaned to [[Central Español]] in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Central se refuerza |language=Spanish |trans-title=Central adds a new player |url=http://cefc.com.uy/wp/central-se-refuerza/ |work=cefc.com.uy |date=12 September 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014172220/http://cefc.com.uy/wp/central-se-refuerza/ |archivedate=14 October 2014 |df= }}</ref> In this team, he appeared in 8 games and scored 3 goals. At the end of the loan, he returned to [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]].

==International career==
San Martín was part of the squad of the [[Uruguay national under-17 football team|Uruguay U-17]] that took part in the [[2011 South American Under-17 Football Championship|2011 South American U17]] in Ecuador and in the [[2011 FIFA U-17 World Cup]], playing five matches and scoring once.<ref>{{cite news|title=Juan San Martin profile|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=332907/index.html|work=FIFA.com}}</ref>

